      <hedline>
        <hl1>Playing Beethoven At Mauthausen</hl1>
      </hedline>
      <abstract>
        <p>Robert A Meister letter on May 9 report on controversial concert performance of Beethoven's Ninth Symphony at Mauthausen, Austria, site of Nazi death camp</p>
      </abstract>
    </body.head>
    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Dissonance in the Shadow of Death'' (Arts pages, May 9):</p>
      </block>
      <block class="full_text">
        <p>To the Editor:</p>
        <p>Re ''Dissonance in the Shadow of Death'' (Arts pages, May 9):</p>
        <p>I cried when I saw the picture of the quarry where Beethoven's Ninth Symphony was played, on the site of the Nazis' death camp at Mauthausen, Austria. Erecting a stylish stage there defiles the memory of some 105,000 who were murdered there and the millions killed in other camps.</p>
        <p>And playing the symphony in a place where only the deepest sorrow is appropriate both desecrates the victims and despoils Beethoven's love of joy and freedom.</p>
        <p>ROBERT A. MEISTER  New York, May 9, 2000</p>
      </block>
    </body.content>
